ENTRY            A0142   20260310   20260508   20260508       A133
SUBENT        A0142001   20260310   20260508   20260508       A133
BIB                 14         60
TITLE      The N-15(p,alpha0)C-12 reaction of stellar energies
AUTHOR     (A.Redder, H.W.Becker, H.Lorenz-Wirzba, C.Rolfs,
           P.Schmalbrock, H.P.Trautvetter)
REFERENCE  (J,ZP/A,305,325,1982)
           (T,LORENZ-WIRZBA,1978) Thesis, Univer. Munster (1978)
REL-REF    (O,O2647001,H.Lorenz-Wirzba+,J,NP/A,313,346,1979)
           Cross section data for 18O(p,alpha)15N
           (O,O2648001,H.Lorenz-Wirzba,T,LORENZ-WIRZBA,1978)
           Cross section data for 19F(p,alpha)16O
           (M,,T.Freye+,J,ZP/A,281,211,1977) - the beam energy
           spread and the energy stability for this accelerator
           have been described in detail.
           (A,C0644001,A.Schardt+,J,PR,86,527,1952)
           (D,C0645001,J.L.Zyskind+,J,NP/A,320,404,1979)
INSTITUTE  (2GERMST)
FACILITY   (CCW,2GERMST) HVEC 350 kV implantation unit used at the
           energy range of Ep=72-355 keV
           (CCW,2GERMNZ) The 1 MV accelerator used at the energy
           range Ep = 350-810 keV
METHOD     (SITA,BCINT,EXTB)
MONITOR    (7-N-15(P,A)6-C-12,,SIG)
            The absolute cross section was determined at
           Ep=353.4keV relative to the Rutherford elastic
           scattering cross section for detection angles
           of 22.5 - 150. degr. A total set of 7 values was
           obtained, which lead to a weighted average of 87/+-4 mb
           This value has been used as the standard in the
           normalization of the excitation functions
MONIT-REF  (,A.Redder,T,REDDER,1982) Diploma, Univer. Muenster
DETECTOR   (SIBAR) Two Si surface barrier detectors (with an
           active area of 300 mm2)
SAMPLE     Supersonic jet target. 15N enriched nitrogen gas at
           inlet pressures of p0 =0.79 to 1.41 bar.
           The Ti15N targets were fabricated by vacuum evaporation
           of a layer of natural Ti onto a 0.25 mm thick
           Ta backing and then by conversion of the Ti film to
           the nitride in an atmosphere of 99% enriched 15N
           gas by resistance heating of the coated Ta backing.
ANALYSIS   The angle-integrated alpha-yields were presented from
           80 - 353 keV, result from experiments on Muenster
           accelerator
            The angle-integrated reaction yields were determined
           using expression W(theta)=1+a1(Ep)cos(theta) from
           the yields observed at 90.degr. in the experiments
           on the 1 MV Mainz accelerator (Ep(lab) = 350-810 keV).
ADD-RES    (ANGD) Angular distribution measurements of the
           15N(p,alpha)12C reaction have been carried out with
           Ti15N solid targets at six energies in the range of
           Ep= 149 to 750 keV. They were described by the
           expression W(theta) = 1 + a1(Ep)cos(theta).
           Thus a1(Ep) was calculated to be equal
                                   0.50-0.53/360 x Ep (Ep in keV).
HISTORY    (19820812C)
           (19991022A) Corrections in A0142.002. Lower case.
           (20011010U) Last checking has been done.
           (20011010A) Date is corrected
           (20200531A) SD: Major corrections in all Subents.
           Subent 003 added.
           (20260310A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
           Subent 004 added.
ENDBIB              60
COMMON               3          3
EN-NRM     MONIT      MONIT-ERR
KEV        MB         MB
  353.4       87.        4.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           67
SUBENT        A0142002   20260310   20260508   20260508       A133
BIB                  5         15
REACTION   (7-N-15(P,A)6-C-12,PAR,SIG)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Error (=5%, except where quoted) includes
           uncertainties in:
            * number of counts,
            * absolute cross section and
            * absolute effective beam energy
COMMENT     (By authors) The 15N(p,alpha1)12C reaction is
           unimportant at stellar energy in comparison to the
           15N(p,alpha0)12C reaction.
STATUS     (TABLE,,A.Redder+,J,ZP/A,305,325,1982) Tbl.1
HISTORY    (20200531A) SD: SF5=PAR added; SF9=EXP deleted from
           REACTION code. BIB updated. Values at EN-ERR corrected
           according to footnote of the table. Value at
           Ep=136.8 keV corrected.
           (20260310U) SD: STATUS updated.
ENDBIB              15
